Looks like the button and each tickbox is triggering an event properly.
Now I have to make it so that the POST route in Python can tell if the
event was triggered by the button or a tickbox, and run corresponding actions
accordingly.

===============================
GPT4 suggestions:
===============================

HTML:
<input type="checkbox" id="myCheckbox" name="myCheckbox" value="Checked">
<button id="myButton">Click me</button>


JavaScript:
document.getElementById('myCheckbox').addEventListener('change', function() {
    if(this.checked) {
        fetch('/myroute', {
            method: 'POST',
            headers: {
                'Content-Type': 'application/json'
            },
            body: JSON.stringify({ action: 'checkbox' })
        });
    }
});

document.getElementById('myButton').addEventListener('click', function() {
    fetch('/myroute', {
            method: 'POST',
            headers: {
                'Content-Type': 'application/json'
            },
            body: JSON.stringify({ action: 'button' })
        });
});

Python:
from flask import Flask, request
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/myroute', methods=['POST'])
def myroute():
    data = request.get_json()
    if data['action'] == 'checkbox':
        # Code to run when checkbox is checked
    elif data['action'] == 'button':
        # Code to run when button is clicked
    return 'Success!', 200

